  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Atradius, TA for Solvency II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South African state credit insurer is ECIC SA, a state controlled entity. ECIC is facing challenges meeting the Solvency II requirements. The Solvency II Directive (2009/138EC) is an EU Directive that codifies and harmonizes the EU insurance regulation. Primarily this concerns the amount of capital that EU insurance companies must hold to reduce the risk of insolvency. Through international agreements Solvency II also applies to South African credit insurance by ECIC both for its commercial (i.e. short term credit insurance) and state covered (i.e. long term insurance) activities.Although South Africa has a well developed financial sector. Solvency II requirements are tough and would demand a substantial effort by ECIC to meet. In essence the question is how to properly calculate the risk for a relatively small long term insurance portfolio.Atradius Dutch State Business N.V. has been commissioned to carry out this project. Credit Insurance company Atradius operates both on a commercial basis and as an implementing entity on behalf of the Dutch state (i.e. Atradius State Business). Atradius is acknowledged internationally for its technical knowledge, product development and risk management. The project will facilitate a specialised training activity for one or two ECIC staff members by Atradius Dutch State Business N.V. in the Netherlands for a maximum of five days.</narrative>
  </description>
